-[TRANQUIL MUSIC]

02:08.215 --> 02:10.042
-[CAT CALLING]

02:48.907 --> 02:51.301
-[PHONE RINGING]

02:51.432 --> 02:52.955
-TOWER 27.

02:53.085 --> 02:54.870
-NEWMIE, SOMETHING'S GOING
ON OVER AT THE SHOWERS,

02:55.000 --> 02:56.611
WILL YOU WATCH MY WATER
WHILE I CHECK IT OUT?

02:56.741 --> 02:58.134
-YOU GOT IT.

03:10.973 --> 03:12.714
-WHY DO I ALWAYS
GET THE NUT CASES?

03:13.932 --> 03:18.372
-[MEN MUMBLING
OVER ONE ANOTHER]

03:38.957 --> 03:41.917
[GROANING IN DISAPPOINTMENT]

03:42.047 --> 03:43.353
-HIT THE BUTTON,
HIT THE BUTTON.

03:44.093 --> 03:45.964
-LET'S BREAK IT UP,
GUYS. SHOW'S OVER.

03:46.095 --> 03:48.358
COME ON, GUYS. BREAK IT UP.

03:49.446 --> 03:52.406
EXCUSE ME, MA'AM,
BUT YOU'RE GONNA HAVE
TO PUT YOUR TOP BACK ON.

03:53.189 --> 03:55.104
-I WAS JUST TRYING
TO GET THE SAND OFF.

03:55.235 --> 03:58.063
-I KNOW, BUT YOU'RE
IN VIOLATION OF OUR
COUNTY ORDINANCE.

03:58.194 --> 04:01.241
-YOU'RE NOT GONNA
ARREST ME, ARE YOU?

04:01.371 --> 04:02.633
-OH, COME ON, LEAVE HER ALONE.

04:02.764 --> 04:04.069
-GO BACK TO YOUR TOWER.

04:04.200 --> 04:06.637
-GIVE ME A BREAK, GUYS.

04:06.768 --> 04:10.685
-LOOK, COULDN'T YOU JUST GIVE
ME A WARNING THIS ONE TIME?

04:12.077 --> 04:14.036
-OKAY, BUT NEXT TIME,
YOU'LL BE LOOKING

04:14.166 --> 04:15.603
AT A $250 FINE.

04:15.733 --> 04:16.778
-WE'LL PAY THE FINE.

04:16.908 --> 04:18.606
-MAN: YEAH,
I GOT TEN BUCKS.

04:18.736 --> 04:22.174
-[BOYS TALKING
OVER ONE ANOTHER]

04:22.305 --> 04:23.567
-MAN: THEN
AGAIN, YOU CAN JUST COME

04:23.698 --> 04:25.700
TO MY HOUSE AND SHOWER.

04:27.832 --> 04:29.007
-MAN: HERE,
I'LL HOLD THE TOWEL.

04:29.138 --> 04:30.618
-MAN 2: OH, COME ON!

04:41.629 --> 04:42.717
-OKAY.

04:44.675 --> 04:46.155
-MAN: HEY, THANK YOU.

04:47.809 --> 04:51.682
-THANKS, YOU'VE
BEEN REALLY SWEET.

04:54.250 --> 04:56.861
-[BOYS TALKING
OVER ONE ANOTHER]

04:59.647 --> 05:03.955
-[SMOOTH POP MUSIC]

05:09.787 --> 05:12.355
-SO LONG, SUCKERS.

05:13.095 --> 05:15.924
-[SCOFFS] THANKS A LOT, DUDE.

05:23.366 --> 05:24.628
-NEWMIE!

05:26.108 --> 05:28.066
-WHAT WAS ALL THE FUSS ABOUT?

05:28.197 --> 05:29.590
-YOU SHOULD'VE
SEEN IT, THIS GIRL
WAS TAKING A TOPLESS SHOWER.

05:29.720 --> 05:32.332
-I SUPPOSE YOU MADE
HER GET DRESSED?

05:32.462 --> 05:33.594
-YEAH.

05:33.724 --> 05:36.118
-ROOKIE MISTAKE, YOU'LL LEARN.

05:36.248 --> 05:39.077
HEY, BY THE WAY,
WHERE'S MY 20 BUCKS?

05:39.208 --> 05:40.340
-WHAT 20 BUCKS?

05:40.470 --> 05:42.733
-USC-UCLA GAME LAST SATURDAY?

05:43.734 --> 05:45.606
-OH, THAT 20 BUCKS.

05:45.736 --> 05:47.999
IT'S IN MY TOWER,
I'LL GO GET IT.

05:54.658 --> 05:55.746
WHAT?

05:56.312 --> 05:57.357
-WHAT'S WRONG?

06:00.621 --> 06:02.057
-I CAN'T FIND MY WALLET.

06:02.187 --> 06:03.928
-MAYBE YOU LEFT IT INSIDE.

06:04.494 --> 06:05.452
-OH, THIS IS GREAT.

06:05.582 --> 06:07.367
I JUST CASHED MY PAY CHECK.

06:08.759 --> 06:10.326
DAMN IT!

06:11.327 --> 06:13.198
YOU DIDN'T SEE ANYBODY
GO INTO MY TOWER?

06:13.329 --> 06:15.549
-I WAS WATCHING YOUR WATER.

06:17.333 --> 06:19.248
-I CAN'T BELIEVE I
JUST GOT RIPPED OFF.

06:19.770 --> 06:21.772
-YOU'RE NOT THE ONLY ONE.
WE GOT RIPPED OFF, TOO.

06:21.903 --> 06:23.470
-WHAT?

06:23.600 --> 06:24.427
-WE ALL GOT BURNED,
MAN, THEY GOT MY WALKMAN,

06:24.558 --> 06:25.428
MY SUNGLASSES.

06:25.559 --> 06:26.864
-MY WATCH, MY GAMEBOY.

06:26.995 --> 06:27.996
-YOU GOTTA DO SOMETHING, BRO.

06:28.126 --> 06:29.519
THIS IS LIKE TOTALLY RUDE, DUDE.

06:29.650 --> 06:30.912
-RIGHT, MAN!

06:32.566 --> 06:34.045
-THAT'S MR. DUDE.

06:35.177 --> 06:36.744
-WHATEVER.

06:37.397 --> 06:39.616
-MAN: YEAH, I
SEE HIM, HE'S DOWN THERE.

06:41.618 --> 06:43.185
-YOU SEE, THE BEAUTY
OF IT IS YOU CAN TAKE

06:43.315 --> 06:45.666
OFF RIGHT ON THE BEACH, CRUISE
TWO FEET ABOVE THE WAVES

06:45.796 --> 06:48.712
OR CLIMB TO 10,000 FEET
AND THEN WHEN YOU'RE DONE,

06:48.843 --> 06:50.714
YOU JUST THROW IT RIGHT
INTO THE BACK OF YOUR TRUCK.

06:50.845 --> 06:53.587
-EVERY LIFEGUARD SHOULD
HAVE ONE, NO DOUBT ABOUT IT.

06:53.717 --> 06:55.589
-SOMEDAY THEY WILL.

06:55.719 --> 06:58.809
-YEAH, NO WAY WE CAN
AFFORD THIS THING.

06:58.940 --> 07:01.551
WE CAN BARELY AFFORD
NEW RESCUE CANS.

07:01.682 --> 07:03.466
-I REALIZE YOU'RE A
LITTLE STRAPPED FOR FUNDS.

07:03.597 --> 07:05.425
I MEAN, WHO ISN'T?

07:05.555 --> 07:09.341
BUT I WANT YOU TO SEE THE
POTENTIAL OF THE PARA-MOTOR.

07:10.821 --> 07:12.910
WHY DON'T YOU TAKE
IT FOR A SPIN?

07:13.041 --> 07:14.738
-SPIN, HUH?

07:14.869 --> 07:16.697
-I CAN TEACH YOU THE
BASICS IN FIVE MINUTES.

07:16.827 --> 07:18.220
YOU SAID YOU'VE
FLOWN A HANG GLIDER,

07:18.350 --> 07:20.091
IT'S PRACTICALLY THE SAME THING.

07:20.222 --> 07:22.485
ONLY YOU DON'T HAVE TO JUMP
OFF A CLIFF TO GET IT GOING.

07:25.836 --> 07:27.055
WHAT DO YOU SAY, MITCH?

07:27.185 --> 07:28.360
NO PRESSURE TO BUY,
I JUST WANT YOU

07:28.491 --> 07:30.319
TO CATCH A GLIMPSE
OF THE FUTURE.

07:30.450 --> 07:32.539
-[MITCH CHUCKLING]

07:40.068 --> 07:42.897
-THEY GOT MY MONEY,
MY PURSE, EVERYTHING.

07:53.385 --> 07:55.605
-WELL, IT WAS ALL A SET UP.
THE SHOWER WAS A DIVERSION.

07:55.736 --> 07:57.259
-SO, YOU THINK WHILE
EVERYONE WAS OVER THERE

07:57.389 --> 07:59.870
WITH THEIR TONGUES HANGING
OUT, SHE HAD A PARTNER

08:00.001 --> 08:00.828
WORKING THE SAND?

08:01.698 --> 08:03.091
-YEAH, I GUESS.

08:03.831 --> 08:05.572
-YEAH, I THINK YOU'RE RIGHT.

08:05.702 --> 08:08.139
UNFORTUNATELY, NONE
OF THE OTHER VICTIMS

08:08.270 --> 08:09.663
COULD GIVE US A VERY
GOOD DESCRIPTION.

08:09.793 --> 08:11.534
AT LEAST NOT OF HER
FACIAL FEATURES.

08:11.665 --> 08:14.755
-EXCUSE ME, BUT I KNOW
WHAT SHE LOOKS LIKE, OKAY?

08:14.885 --> 08:16.365
-WELL, THEN MAYBE
YOU OUGHT TO SIT DOWN

08:16.496 --> 08:17.453
WITH A POLICE SKETCH ARTIST.

08:18.323 --> 08:21.413
-WHAT FOR? WHAT ARE THE
CHANCES OF YOU CATCHING HER?

08:21.544 --> 08:24.199
-WELL, I KNOW IT'S A LONG
SHOT, BUT YOU NEVER KNOW

08:24.329 --> 08:26.375
HOW THINGS WILL SIZE UP.

08:26.506 --> 08:28.943
-NO, THANKS, IT'S NOT
WORTH THE HUMILIATION,

08:29.073 --> 08:30.553
BUT I APPRECIATE IT.

08:30.684 --> 08:33.600
-HEY, I'M HERE TO
SERVE AND PROTECT.

08:34.861 --> 08:37.908
[LAUGHING]

08:42.870 --> 08:43.827
-OKAY, YOU COMFORTABLE?

08:43.957 --> 08:45.350
-YEAH, YEAH, IT FEELS GOOD.

08:45.481 --> 08:47.570
-OKAY, I NEED YOU TO RUN
HARD UNTIL THE GLIDER'S

08:47.701 --> 08:50.181
UP OVER YOUR HEAD AND DON'T
LET UP ON THE THROTTLE

08:50.312 --> 08:52.793
UNTIL YOU'RE AT LEAST 200
FEET IN THE AIR, OKAY?

08:52.923 --> 08:53.794
-OKAY.

08:54.621 --> 08:55.883
-IT'S A BREEZE.

08:56.013 --> 08:57.537
-OKAY, LET'S GO.

08:57.667 --> 09:03.151
-[MOTOR ROARING]

09:32.659 --> 09:34.486
-HOW YOU DOING, MITCH?

09:37.098 --> 09:40.405
-GREAT. UNBELIEVABLE.

09:41.319 --> 09:43.017
HOW LONG CAN I STAY UP?

09:43.713 --> 09:46.455
-OH, ABOUT AN HOUR,
HOUR AND A HALF.

09:47.456 --> 09:48.849
GO ON, HAVE A GOOD TIME.

09:48.979 --> 09:52.809
-YOU GOT IT. WOO!

10:05.256 --> 10:08.433
[CHUCKLES] LOOK AT THAT, WOO!

10:11.393 --> 10:13.395
[CHUCKLING]

10:20.141 --> 10:22.883
-UNREAL, WOO.

11:01.530 --> 11:05.012
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

11:05.708 --> 11:08.624
-THIS IS BUCHANNON.
CAN YOU READ ME?

11:08.755 --> 11:10.800
-YEAH, LOUD AND CLEAR.

11:10.931 --> 11:12.889
-PATCH ME THROUGH
TO THE SCARAB.

11:13.020 --> 11:15.065
-OKAY, HOLD ON, IT
MIGHT TAKE ME A MINUTE.

11:19.983 --> 11:22.725
-[GIRL CRIES OUT]

11:22.856 --> 11:24.553
-HEY!

11:39.350 --> 11:41.570
-CAROLINE: THIS IS
SCARAB ONE, COME IN, MITCH.

11:41.701 --> 11:44.791
-YEAH, CAROLINE,
WHAT'S YOUR LOCATION?

11:46.749 --> 11:49.404
-WE'RE ABOUT TWO
MILES OFF POINT DUME.

11:49.534 --> 11:51.362
-HEAD SOUTH, ASAP.

11:51.493 --> 11:53.538
-WHAT'S GOING ON,
MITCH, WHERE ARE YOU?

11:53.669 --> 11:56.498
-YOU'LL SEE ME
WHEN YOU GET HERE.

11:58.892 --> 12:03.940
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

12:12.819 --> 12:17.214
-CAROLINE, IT'S MITCH, I
GOT A VICTIM ON A RAFT

12:17.345 --> 12:18.738
WHO'S ABOUT TO GO UNDER.

12:18.868 --> 12:20.174
YOU BETTER STEP ON IT.

12:26.833 --> 12:31.751
-[CRYING]

12:41.717 --> 12:44.502
-WHAT THE HECK IS THAT THING?

12:48.245 --> 12:51.727
OH, MY GOD, IT'S MITCH!

12:52.684 --> 12:54.164
WHERE'D HE GET THAT?

12:59.343 --> 13:02.303
-[CRYING]

13:04.087 --> 13:05.393
-OVER THERE,

13:05.523 --> 13:07.351
A LIFE RAFT.
-I SEE IT, I SEE IT.

13:08.004 --> 13:10.702
-[CRYING]

13:35.597 --> 13:38.252
-I GOT YOU. I GOT YOU.

13:38.948 --> 13:41.211
-VICTIM RECOVERED, KMF295, OUT.

13:43.910 --> 13:46.695
-COME ON. YOU'RE OKAY.

13:52.179 --> 13:54.572
-ALL RIGHT. [LAUGHS]

14:04.278 --> 14:06.802
-IT'S ALL RIGHT,
WHAT HAPPENED TO YOU?

14:06.933 --> 14:09.239
WHY WERE YOU IN THE
RAFT? DID YOUR BOAT SINK?

14:10.675 --> 14:13.504
YOU DON'T SPEAK ENGLISH?
SHE DOESN'T SPEAK ENGLISH.

14:13.635 --> 14:15.985
-[SPEAKING CHINESE]

14:16.116 --> 14:18.422
-THAT'S CHINESE.

14:18.945 --> 14:22.949
-IT'S OKAY, COME HERE. IT'S
OKAY, YOU'RE GONNA BE OKAY.

14:25.386 --> 14:27.431
-SHE LOOKS PRETTY DEHYDRATED,
LET'S GET SOME VITALS.

14:27.562 --> 14:29.216
-OKAY, YOU'RE GONNA BE OKAY.

14:29.346 --> 14:30.739
YOU'RE GONNA BE OKAY.

14:30.870 --> 14:33.524
-[SPEAKING CHINESE]

14:33.655 --> 14:35.700
-WHERE DO YOU THINK
SHE'S FROM, MITCH?

14:35.831 --> 14:38.790
-MY GUESS, IMMIGRATION
SMUGGLING SHIP.

14:38.921 --> 14:41.010
BIG BUSINESS LAST YEAR.

14:41.141 --> 14:43.317
COAST GUARD PICKED UP OVER
2,500 CHINESE REFUGEES

14:43.447 --> 14:45.275
IN THE LAST TWO YEARS.

14:46.450 --> 14:49.758
-WHAT IS YOUR NAME? YOUR NAME.

14:50.454 --> 14:55.198
I'M CAROLINE. CAROLINE, MITCH.

14:55.329 --> 14:58.027
CAROLINE, WHO ARE YOU,
WHAT IS YOUR NAME?

14:59.942 --> 15:01.509
-SUN YI.

15:02.379 --> 15:05.165
-SUN YI, OKAY, GOOD.

15:05.295 --> 15:06.993
THAT'S HER NAME, MITCH. SUN YI.

15:07.123 --> 15:08.516
HER NAME'S SUN YI.

15:08.646 --> 15:11.301
-WELCOME TO BAYWATCH, SUN YI.

15:12.650 --> 15:14.348
100 OVER 60.

15:14.478 --> 15:17.177
-MITCH, THERE'S BEEN NO SIGN
OF ANYBODY ELSE IN RAFTS.

15:17.307 --> 15:18.221
THE COAST GUARD HAS
PLANES AND CUTTERS

15:18.352 --> 15:19.266
SEARCHING OFF SHORE.

15:19.396 --> 15:20.267
-GREAT.

15:20.397 --> 15:21.398
-MITCH, COME HERE.

15:24.184 --> 15:26.490
DO YOU WANT ME TO CALL
THE IMMIGRATION OFFICE?

15:26.621 --> 15:28.275
-WELL, I THINK WE HAVE TO.

15:30.103 --> 15:32.018
-WAIT A MINUTE, YOU
GUYS ARE GONNA TURN HER

15:32.148 --> 15:34.107
OVER TO THE INS?

15:34.759 --> 15:36.500
NO, YOU CAN'T DO THAT.

15:36.631 --> 15:38.024
I MEAN, WE DON'T
EVEN KNOW FOR SURE

15:38.154 --> 15:39.677
IF SHE'S AN ILLEGAL IMMIGRANT.

15:39.808 --> 15:41.766
-CAROLINE, I THINK IT'S
A PRETTY FAIR ASSUMPTION.

15:41.897 --> 15:43.943
-NO, NO, THAT'S NOT TRUE.

15:44.073 --> 15:46.075
MITCH, WHAT DO WE
REALLY KNOW ABOUT HER?

15:46.206 --> 15:48.121
I MEAN, WE KNOW THAT
SHE'S DEHYDRATED.

15:48.251 --> 15:50.340
SHE PROBABLY HASN'T
EATEN IN DAYS.

15:51.298 --> 15:52.255
MITCH, LOOK AT HER.

15:53.082 --> 15:54.779
-MAN: WHAT ARE WE
SUPPOSED TO DO WITH HER?

15:57.957 --> 16:00.176
-SHE'S PROBABLY
SCARED TO DEATH.

16:09.403 --> 16:11.361
-WHAT, WHAT IS IT?

16:12.362 --> 16:13.798
BACK OF AN ENVELOPE.

16:14.756 --> 16:15.713
THERE'S AN ADDRESS ON HERE.

16:15.844 --> 16:18.238
951 AND A HALF HILL STREET.

16:18.368 --> 16:20.370
-ISN'T THERE A HILL
STREET IN CHINATOWN?

16:20.501 --> 16:22.329
-YEAH, YEAH, SURE.

16:23.156 --> 16:25.680
WHAT IS THIS?

16:26.898 --> 16:28.248
WHAT IS THIS? IS THIS A NAME?

16:28.378 --> 16:29.553
NAME?

16:29.684 --> 16:31.991
-LIN-WA CHOU.

16:33.862 --> 16:35.081
-LIN-WA CHOU

16:35.211 --> 16:36.778
-[SPEAKING CHINESE]

16:42.827 --> 16:44.525
-EXCUSE ME, COULD I
TALK TO YOU FOR A SECOND?

16:44.655 --> 16:46.396
-[MAN GRUNTING]

16:49.573 --> 16:51.836
-COULD YOU TELL ME
WHERE THIS ADDRESS IS?

16:53.447 --> 16:55.405
NOBODY SPEAKS ENGLISH.

16:56.406 --> 17:01.107
951, 951, 951 AND
A HALF HILL STREET.

17:01.237 --> 17:02.717
-[KNOCKING DOOR]

17:07.200 --> 17:10.420
-HI, I'M LOOKING FOR THE
PERSON WHO WROTE THIS.

17:11.204 --> 17:13.902
951 AND A HALF
HILL STREET, RIGHT?

17:17.036 --> 17:19.951
THE NAME IS LIN-WA
CHOU? LIN-WA CHOU?

17:20.082 --> 17:21.953
-MAN: [SPEAKING CHINESE]

17:26.522 --> 17:31.354
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

17:38.796 --> 17:40.407
-LIN-WA!

17:45.803 --> 17:46.804
HEY!

17:56.597 --> 18:00.383
[GROANING]

18:18.749 --> 18:20.882
-YOU KNOW, TANYA HARDING
COULD'VE USED A GUY LIKE YOU.

18:21.012 --> 18:22.144
-[SPEAKING CHINESE]

18:25.800 --> 18:26.975
WHY ARE YOU LOOKING FOR ME?

18:27.845 --> 18:29.195
-ARE YOU LIN-WA CHOU ?

18:30.109 --> 18:31.110
-WHO ARE YOU?

18:32.198 --> 18:35.636
-MY NAME IS MITCH BUCHANNON,
I'M NOT WITH THE INS.

18:36.680 --> 18:38.900
I'M AN LA COUNTY LIFEGUARD.

18:39.509 --> 18:42.295
WE RESCUED A CHINESE WOMAN
ON A RAFT THIS MORNING.

18:42.817 --> 18:44.384
SHE HAD THIS IN HER POCKET.

18:49.650 --> 18:50.999
-IS SHE ALL RIGHT?
WHERE IS SHE?

18:51.652 --> 18:52.870
-YOU KNOW HER?

18:53.523 --> 18:54.785
-SHE'S MY SISTER.

18:55.612 --> 18:56.613
-YOUR SISTER?

18:56.744 --> 18:58.267
-WHERE IS SHE? CAN I SEE HER?

18:59.660 --> 19:02.141
-WELL, IF I CAN MAKE
IT TO MY CAR, YEAH.

19:02.880 --> 19:06.797
-[SPEAKING CHINESE]

19:09.365 --> 19:11.019
-I'M SORRY IF THEY
CAUSED YOU ANY HARM.

19:11.150 --> 19:14.109
THE PEOPLE IN THIS NEIGHBORHOOD
LOOK OUT FOR EACH OTHER.

19:14.240 --> 19:17.373
-IT'S OKAY, IT'S
PROBABLY JUST A BRUISE.

19:17.504 --> 19:20.550
COME ON. [GROANS]

19:24.250 --> 19:26.513
-CAROLINE: NO, NO,
IT'S OKAY, IT'S OKAY.

19:26.643 --> 19:28.558
[BEEPING]

19:29.211 --> 19:32.475
OH, BOY. YOUR TEMPERATURE'S
103, THAT'S PRETTY HIGH.

19:33.563 --> 19:35.086
OKAY, I WANT YOU TO LIE DOWN.

19:35.217 --> 19:37.785
I'M GONNA PUT SOME COLD
CLOTHS ON YOUR HEAD, OKAY?

19:37.915 --> 19:39.917
IT'S OKAY, IT'S ALL RIGHT.

19:40.048 --> 19:41.571
I'M SORRY, I'M SORRY.

19:41.702 --> 19:43.747
IT HURTS WHEN I TOUCH
YOU THERE, OKAY.

19:43.878 --> 19:46.750
GIVE ME YOUR HAND, GIVE ME
YOUR HAND. IT'S ALL RIGHT.

19:50.319 --> 19:52.060
-MITCH: SUN YI.

19:53.409 --> 19:57.108
-[UPLIFTING MUSIC]

20:03.941 --> 20:09.773
-[SPEAKING CHINESE]

20:11.427 --> 20:12.907
-IT'S HER SISTER.

20:13.995 --> 20:17.955
-WAY TO GO, MITCH. YOU'RE A
HELL OF A GUY, YOU KNOW THAT?

20:18.608 --> 20:20.523
-MITCH: SHE FEELING ALL RIGHT?

20:21.176 --> 20:23.874
-ACTUALLY, NO, SHE'S RUNNING
A REALLY HIGH TEMPERATURE.

20:24.005 --> 20:26.137
SHE'S EXPERIENCING
ABDOMINAL PAINS.

20:26.268 --> 20:28.270
I'M AFRAID SHE MIGHT
BE REALLY SICK, MITCH.

20:28.401 --> 20:29.315
-[CRYING]

20:30.272 --> 20:31.273
-[MITCH GROANING]

20:32.361 --> 20:33.884
-WHAT HAPPENED TO YOU?

20:34.015 --> 20:35.495
-IT'S A LONG STORY.

20:35.625 --> 20:39.194
I GOT WHACKED IN THE
